scroll: test-distill-production
description: Test distill primitive with production backend

requires:
  input_text:
    type: string
    default: |
      Microservices architecture is a software development approach that structures an application
      as a collection of loosely coupled services. Each service is fine-grained and implements a
      single business capability. Services can be developed, deployed, and scaled independently.
      They communicate through well-defined APIs, typically REST or message queues. This approach
      enables teams to work autonomously on different services, using different technologies if needed.
      The main benefits include improved scalability, fault isolation, and faster deployment cycles.
      However, microservices also introduce complexity in terms of distributed system management,
      service discovery, and data consistency across services.

steps:
  - distill:
      input: ${input_text}
      intensity: balanced
      output_contract:
        length: sentence
        format: prose
    output: result
